The paper deals with a cognitive scenario involving spectrum sharing between a primary user and an energy harvesting secondary user. The paper discusses the modeling of energy harvesting and data queues, and the stability region of the proposed system. The paper's focus on energy harvesting and queueing theory suggests that it is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. The paper's use of Markov processes and numerical analysis suggests that it may also belong to the Mathematical Analysis (cs.MA) and Game Theory (cs.GT) sub-categories.
